<div id="panel-what-is-omg">
   <div class="panel-content">
      <h3>What is OpenMusic.Gallery?</h3>
      <p>OpenMusic.Gallery is a platform for making and sharing <b>open music</b>.</p>
            
   </div>            
</div>

<div id="panel-what-is-open-music">
      <div class="panel-content">
   
         <h3>What is "open music"?</h3>
         <p>Like open source software, but applied to music. <b>Open music</b> comes with its "source code".</p>
         <p>You can change the tempo, the key, the levels, the FX, and the individual notes.</p>
      </div>            
</div>
   

<div id="panel-how-it-works">
   <div class="panel-content">
      <h3>How does it work?</h3>

      <p>Sound files on the Internet can be arranged into drumbeats and melodies, which 
         can be combined to make larger works of music. 
      </p>
      <div id="drum-example"></div>

      <p>You can click "Remix" on anything in the gallery to make your own version.</p>
   </div>
</div>

<div>
